| Summary         = Turbo Granny fails to obtain any information, but they are helped by Rokuro, exiled as a defective clone; after a brief fight with Bega, he learns the missing {{Transliteration|ja|kintama}} was picked up by Unji Zuma, a student at Renjaku, a local high school infamous for its delinquent students. A street gang from Renjaku tell Momo and Okarun that Zuma entered a detailed diorama filled with monsters a week ago; Zuma vowed to defeat the diorama-world using the power of the {{Transliteration|ja|kintama}}. Momo inadvertently falls into the diorama-world, which is a board game named Danmanra. Although her telekinesis is disabled in Danmanra, she meets Zuma, who can use [[oil-paper umbrella]]-based {{Transliteration|ja|yōkai}} powers when he holds the {{Transliteration|ja|kintama}}. Zuma defeats a powerful knight [[Boss (video games)|boss]] but then loses the {{translit|ja|kintama}} and works with Momo to retrieve it, moving through an obstacle course guarded by frog {{Transliteration|ja|[[shikigami]]}}. They are forced to play the {{Ill|color demon|ja|いろ鬼}} variant of tag, which requires them to touch the food announced by a massive chef boss.
