| Summary         = At home, Momo tends Okarun's wounds and they eat a meal cooked by Vamola, who points out their obvious mutual attraction. Okarun asks Momo on a date after she loses two [[staring contest]]s; outraged, she calls him a creep and he chides himself for moving too fast. Okarun, Aira, and Jiji meet Momo and Vamola on the way to school; the fresh rift between Okarun and Momo leads to an awkward squabble, which stops when Vamola suggests they all go on a group date. While shopping at [[Aeon (company)|Neon Town]], Rin and Kouki are confronted by three Black Paladins: Enenra, Jack Wisp, and Vakappa. Enenra uses his smoke powers to subdue Rin and instructs Kouki to admit defeat to save Rin. Jack Wisp takes her "Lord of the Flies" power using a {{translit|ja|kozuka}} knife and hands it to Enenra, who similarly has Rin submit to save Kouki; Mai disappears along with the "Ombusman" power. Before they can finish off the girls, all three Paladins suddenly rush to the nearest restroom, summoned by a small girl, Miss Hanako, who easily defeats the trio and flushes Jack and Vakappa away, though Enenra escapes. She helped only after Turbo Granny asked. Picking up his {{translit|ja|kozuka}} knives, Enenra vows to kill Jiji. Returning to Ueno, Saint-Germain reports to Sir Vlad, who wants to assemble an "ultimate" {{translit|ja|yokai}} using the Fairy-Tale Card, energized with six powers extracted from the Family: Momo's [[Alice's Adventures in Wonderland|''Alice'']] and Zuma's ''[[Hansel and Gretel]]'', which already were taken by Shinobi Basho while four others remain to be gathered. Basho installs Rin (''[[The Little Mermaid]]'') and Kouki's (''[[Snow White]]'') powers into Vlad. Enenra is surprised when Vlad asks him to yield his power (''[[Little Red Riding Hood]]''). Seiko thanks the masked priests for their help; they confess they asked for help, later realizing one (Basho) had an unfamiliar background. The Yatagarasu priests discuss the Black Paladins with Seiko. At the Super Amusement Park (based on [[Seibu-en]]) group date, Momo and Okarun fight jealous feelings and heartache; a new masked group calling themselves the Dragon Knights vow to take Okarun's power, which is the last needed by Sir Vlad (''[[The Adventures of Pinocchio]]'').
| LineColor       = 5CEE38
