> 202: The priest who led them to the castle is taken hostage by the phantom ninja thief, but Seiko sees through the deception and tells Momo and Vamola to return to the temple; the "priest" is a {{translit|ja|yokai}} seeking to steal their powers for the Serpoians, working with a crew of chameleon-like humanoids, and Seiko stays behind to buy time for Momo's escape.
> 203: Enenra, the ersatz priest, is a smoke {{translit|ja|yokai}} who defeats Granny Seiko, but she refuses to yield and an impatient Evil Eye breaks in, asking how long he needs to wait.
> 204: The Evil Eye's attacks are ineffective, but he manages to save Seiko. Because of his obvious targeting, Evil Eye derisively dubs Enenra "Nug Lover", and Enenra protests, saying he is better known as "The Red Baron". After an internal consultation, Jiji takes over and scores a direct hit with his evil gun attack.
> 205: Jiji and Evil Eye keep switching places to attack and defend, respectively, taking advantage of [[chirality]] to land hits. Enenra insists he will win, but the Evil Eye declares he is a genius and will prevail in the end.
> 206: Jiji/Evil Eye take on a hybrid form by switching rapidly, a technique they worked out to play ''[[Momotaro Dentetsu]]'' together, and Enenra invades their lungs as smoke, but they blast him out using the Evil Gun, ultimately compressing and then ejecting him out through the temple roof. As they walk out, holding Seiko, they reflect that she would have "insta-killed" Enenru had she been healthy.
> 207: One by one, Vamola and Momo take out the ninjas and escape the castle, meeting Jiji and Seiko outside. When the castle reveals itself as the ninja chameleon alien, Momo sacrifices the chance to lift the curse and turns to fight it, telling Jiji to rush Seiko to the hospital.
> 208: The {{translit|ja|kaiju}} suit's endurance is sapped by the ninja chameleon's explosive firework bombs, so Momo and Vamola infiltrate it by using the suit as a decoy, and detonate stolen bombs within the castle in the style of [[Issun-bōshi]].
> 209: As the castle-ninja disintegrates, Momo is separated from Vamola and begins to disappear as she has been forgotten. A squad of masked priests bring her to a waterfall shrine, wrapped in a bamboo leaf, where they use a hammer to restore her size.
> 210: Momo wakes up next to Vamola and sets out to find Seiko; she has forgotten everything, starting from before she first met Okarun, who meanwhile is diligently cleaning the shrine under Manjiro's coaching, convinced that Momo will soon return.
  >>------Potential volume break after nine chapters------<<
> 211: At Tasty Geezer Breads, Count Saint-Germain meets with the frustrated alien, who is working as a baker, and Enenra, who tries to return the {{translit|ja|kozuka}} knives. Enenra is working with Saint-Germain for the Black Paladins, which is a clandestine organization that are hired ostensibly as [[Divination#Japan|diviners]] for companies, but eventually take over using curses; the Serpo have engaged their services, but now Seiko and the Sorcerers Association are aware of their activities. Although they do not trust the Serpo, Saint-Germain decides to try to befriend Okarun to create the ultimate {{translit|ja|yokai}}, as their powers can only be used by humans. Momo's amnesia includes forgetting her friends and how to use her powers.
> 212: Returning to school, Okarun practices exercising his chi, Aira describes Queen Sensei's healing powers; when Momo arrives, Jiji explains she has lost her memory, although her squabbles with Aira seem instinctual. Since Okarun is now a stranger to her, he vows to "call out to her" and rekindle their relationship.
> 213: Fed up with his stalking as he works up the courage to speak with her, Momo confronts Okarun, telling him she knows they used to be friends and even if she can't remember, she was relieved to see him. He promises to put in the effort and rebuild their relationship.
> 214: Feeling alienated by Okarun's refusal to reveal his actual name and the other members of the History and Culture Research Club spouting self-serving lies, Momo is approached by Sanjome, asking to hear her worries.
> 215: Despite being the only one to not remember him, Momo accepts a crime-prevention whistle from Sanjome. Miko and Muko set up Momo on a date with Okarun to see [[Mummy|mummies]] from [[Ancient Egypt]] at the [[National Museum of Nature and Science]] in Ueno Park; after Okarun confesses his love while walking home, they are pulled into an empty space, where they are confronted by a horde of Serpoians.
> 216: Three Serpoians launch an "awesome zone" attack, which Okarun deflects. Their contracted help, Mr. Dris, is wearing an Egyptian funerary mask and his body is wrapped in bandages like a mummy; he is riding a bicycle and wields a sword. Dris uses a special attack which switches anything black to empty space. Okarun saves Momo from a fatal fall and then deflects a sword slash using the ogre club.
> 217: Momo blows the whistle, which summons the frustrated alien to their aid and she begins subduing the Serpoians, albeit reluctantly; Okarun fights off Mr. Dris to allow Momo to escape and find Jiji, but is stabbed as she congratulates him prematurely.
> 218: Momo uses her {{translit|ja|ki}} through Okarun to enlarge the ogre club, cleaving Mr. Dris apart, but he regenerates and extinguishes all the lights, using [[echolocation]] to continue the fight. Okarun and Momo use a dummy to fool him and unwind his bandages, causing his exposed skin to decay.
> 219: ... and he takes his true form, resembling a [[blue whale]], but is unable to support his weight so they use the ogre club to avoid catastrophe. They leave the scene, Momo carried piggyback by Okarun. Seiko wakes up in the hospital to find Turbo Granny has returned.
  >>------Potential volume break after nine chapters------<<
> 220: At home, Momo squeamishly tends to Okarun's wounds and they enjoy a meal cooked by Vamola, who points out their obvious mutual attraction; afterward, Momo loses two [[staring contest]]s so he asks her on a date.
> 221: Outraged, Momo calls Okarun a creep and he withdraws, calling it a joke, but silently castigates himself for moving too fast. At the shrine, Manjiro is surprised that Okarun learned to wield the ogre club and admits the chores were for cleaning, not training. Okarun, Aira, and Jiji meet Momo and Vamola on the way to school; the fresh rift between Okarun and Momo leads to an awkward squabble, which stops when Vamola suggests they all go on a group date. While shopping at [[Aeon (company)|Neon Town]], Rin and Kouki bond over vampires and gothic romance when they are sucked into an empty space and confronted by three Black Paladins led by Enenra (aka The Red Baron, addressed as "Sir Red").
> 222: Jack Wisp, who wears a bowler hat and pumpkin-shaped [[Spanish breeches]], ignites his smelly flatulence; Rin calls on Mai and shields Kouki while manipulating gravity to keep the Paladins away. The Pygmies build a piano for Kouki, but her insects are incinerated by Jack Wisp; she then accompanies Rin to boost their combined powers.
> 223: As they work together, Rin and Mai's costumes adopt insect themes and they overwhelm Wisp. The third Paladin, Vakappa, admires the "powerful and bewitching girls". Enenra uses his smoke powers to seize Rin and asks Kouki to admit defeat to save Rin; as Kouki does so, Jack Wisp pulls out a {{translit|ja|kozuka}} knife and places it on her right hand.
> 224: Jack Wisp takes the "Lord of the Flies" power and hands it to Enenra, who tells Rin to submit lest Kouki drown in Vakappa's grasp. Rin surrenders and Mai disappears along with the "Ombusman" power. Enenra leaves the girls to Jack and Vakappa, but before they can finish, all three Paladins suddenly rush to the nearest restroom to relieve themselves, where they find a small girl who proves resistant to their attacks.
> 225: The girl, Miss Hanako, easily defeats the trio and flushes Jack and Vakappa away, though Enenra escapes. Afterward, she is invited to play by (X), a large beast, but is excused by {{translit|ja|kamikure}}, a humanoid adhered to a western toilet, who tells the beast he helped only after Turbo Granny asked. The beast picks up Rin and Kouki. Picking up his {{translit|ja|kozuka}} knives, Enenra vows to kill Jiji.
> 226: Returning to Ueno, Saint-Germain reports to Sir Vlad, who had hired him to assemble an "ultimate" {{translit|ja|yokai}} using the Fairy-Tale Card, energized with six powers extracted from the Family. Two have been harvested already: Momo's [[Alice's Adventures in Wonderland|''Alice'']] and Zuma's ''[[Hansel and Gretel]]'' while four others remain to be gathered: , ''[[Little Red Riding Hood]]'', ''[[The Little Mermaid]]'', and ''[[The Adventures of Pinocchio]]''. Enenra returns and gives the powers from Rin and Kouki to Shinobi Basho, who had extracted the powers from Momo and Zuma through deception. Basho adds Rin and Kouki's powers into Vlad.
> 227: When Saint-Germain proposes adding another power, Enenra objects and Vlad rebukes him, then proposes that Enenra yields his ''Red Riding Hood'' power to him. Zuma wakes up to the welcome news that Daiki has been restored and returned to his family. Seiko thanks the masked priests for their help; they confess that due to their age, they asked younger people to help out, but later realized one had an unfamiliar background.
> 228: The Yatagarasu priests discuss the Black Paladins with Seiko. At the Super Amusement Park (based on [[Seibu-en]]) group date, Momo and Okarun fight jealous feelings and heartache; a new masked group calling themselves the Dragon Knights vow to take Okarun's ''Pinocchio'' powers.
  >>------Potential volume break after nine chapters------<<
> 229: As the group date continues, Momo and Okarun struggle with jealousy after pairing off with Jiji and Aira. Kinta sits down for a haircut in the park's Showa era marketplace from Yatagarasu, a bearded barber wearing a pompadour, and Vamola, told to wait outside, wanders away toward a food stand.
> 230: Okarun and Aira grow closer in respect and understanding, spontaneously holding hands, as do Momo and Jiji; despite her denial that it is a date, Momo finds herself at ease with him.
> 231: When the two couples pass each other in the hall holding hands, Momo explodes with jealous rage at an overwhelmed Okarun, doubting whether he sincerely liked her. Jiji tries to reassure her and sends her {{translit|ja|chi}}; when they encounter the [[brachiosaurus]] model, it comes to life and swallows him. While waiting, Vamola purchases two [[Shizuoka oden|konnyaku skewers]], and Yatagarasu ushers her into the stall, wearing a now-bloody tunic.
> 232: Chiquitita and Peeny-Weeny also are visiting Super Park, the son showed a marked enthusiasm for dinosaurs. Vamola picks up her konnyaku skewers from the vendor, shown to be a Serpoian, and walks into the sinister barber shop. At the aquarium, Okarun frets that Momo has chosen Jiji and Aira proposes they should become a couple; after they nearly kiss, an eavesdropping sea lion declares he has the heart of a water flea, revealing himself as Blagojević, a tall human wearing a white [[domino mask]].
> 233: The dinosaurs come to life and Momo flees. Silky moves to protect Okarun; the new foes are the Dragon Knights, also known as Vlad's Guard, led by Gillesderais, a masked man dressed in a long white coat wielding large scissors. He is seeking Turbo Granny's powers. When Okarun says that he no longer has them, Gillesderais calls him a liar. Blagojević licks the floor to make it slick and bowls over Silky and Okarun with a body slam.
> 234: Silky and Okarun are quickly subdued by Gillesderais and Blagojević, who ask them to submit and surrender their powers, even though Okarun already has returned Turbo Granny's; one of the Knights reports that Momo and Jiji have been captured, but Vamola and Kinta have disappeared. Yatagarasu arrives, questioning why the Knights have such weird hairdos.
> 235: Yatagarasu says he will cut the Knights' weird hairdos and they attack him with hockey sticks, but he rises and fights back, as he has been asked to protect the Family. He asks Silky to stab her hair into the ground, which he trims into resilient turf to negate Blagojević's slick surface. Gillesderais mocks him, but Yatagarasu deals him a heavy {{translit|ja|shoryuken}} uppercut.
-->

